description.plain:
Gabriel Guerra (b. May 23, 1997), better known by his stage name DJ Scheme, is a well-known producer from Palm Beach, Florida. He has worked with artists like Juice WRLD and Ski Mask the Slump God, and he was also a close friend of the late XXXTENTACION.

In 2019, DJ Scheme released Preseason EP, his three-track long, debut studio EP, the most popular of the three tracks being “How You Feel? (Freestyle).” The EP features vocals from Ski Mask the Slump God, Danny Towers, and Lil Yachty over Scheme’s instrumentals.

DJ Scheme released his collaborative debut studio album, FAMILY, on December 4, 2020. It featured a large variety of artists across its seventeen tracks, including Ski Mask the Slump God, Juice WRLD, Danny Towers, Skrillex, Joey Bada$$, among others.

description.plain:
On “How You Feel? (Freestyle),” Lil Yachty, Ski Mask the Slump God & Danny Towers team up to assist DJ Scheme for the second song of Scheme’s three-track warm-up EP, Preseason EP.

The song, which quickly went viral, finds Ski, Danny, and Boat using their best flows over bass-heavy production handled by Scheme and Ronny J. The music video for the song was released on August, 16, 2019.

The song was later included as the twelfth track of DJ Scheme’s debut studio album, FAMILY.

description.plain:
“E-ER” is a DJ Scheme-hosted collaboration between Ski Mask the Slump God, Danny Towers, and Lil Yachty. The track follows the quartet’s 2019 Gold-certified single “How You Feel? (Freestyle),” a song that marked Scheme’s first hit.

“E-ER” was first previewed during DJ Scheme’s Instagram Live on September 11, 2020. Following the initial tease, the track was previewed many times after. The song leaked in its entirety on November 24, 2020.

description.plain:
This is the original version of “Hey Mister,” which was teased on numerous occasions by all parties involved. This version of the song was expected to appear on Ski Mask and Juice WRLD’s collaborative album, Evil Twins, but whether or not this will occur is unknown.

The official version of the track, which only features Ski Mask, was released on January 16, 2019. This original version, however, was leaked nearly a year later on December 30, 2019.
